Three people died and seven others were injured in a head-on collision between a truck and a mini-bus taxi on the R411 between Mthatha and Mqanduli on Wednesday. Transport department spokesperson Unathi Binqose said all the deceased and injured were traveling in the taxi. “The truck driver escaped unharmed. The injured have been taken to nearby hospitals for medical attention," he said. "The cause of the accident remains unknown at this stage. A culpable homicide docket has been opened.” DispatchLIVE